Play
is
most
important
to
a
child.
All
of
us
must
play
a
little.
All
work
and
no
play
makes
Jack
a
dull
boy,
the
old
saying
goes.
Play
affords
relaxation.
Some
people
claim
their
work
is
so
enthralling
that
they
do
not
need
to
play.
Psychologists
say
that
the
stress
of
modern
life
demands
that
all
adults
have
some
hobby
away
from
their
daily
pursuit.
